definition_en:
The date that the publisher accepted the resource into their system.
To indicate the start of an embargo period, use Accepted or Submitted, as appropriate.

The date the resource is made publicly available. May be a range.
To indicate the end of an embargo period, use Available.
The specific, documented date at which the resource receives a copyrighted status, if applicable.

The date in which the resource content was collected.
To indicate precise or particular timeframes in which research was conducted.

The date range (start date) in which the resource content was collected.
To indicate precise or particular timeframes in which research was conducted.

The date range (end date) in which the resource content was collected.
To indicate precise or particular timeframes in which research was conducted.

The date that the resource content applies to, describes, or covers.
 To indicate the temporal coverage of the resource, use Coverage. This may be different from Collected.

The date range (start date) that the resource content applies to, describes, or covers.
 To indicate the temporal coverage of the resource, use Coverage. This may be different from Collected.

The date range (end date) that the resource content applies to, describes, or covers.
 To indicate the temporal coverage of the resource, use Coverage. This may be different from Collected.

The date the resource itself was put together; this could refer to a timeframe in ancient history, a single date for a final component, e.g., the finalised file with all the data.
Recommended for discovery.

The date the resource itself was put together; this could refer to a timeframe in ancient history, the start date (of the range) for a final component, e.g., the finalised file with all the data.
Recommended for discovery.

The date the resource itself was put together; this could refer to a timeframe in ancient history, the end date (of the range) for a final component, e.g., the finalised file with all the data.
Recommended for discovery.
The date that the resource is published or distributed, e.g., to a data centre.

The date the creator submits the resource to the publisher. This could be different from Accepted if the publisher then applies a selection process.
Recommended for discovery.
The date of the last update to the resource, when the resource is being added to.
The date range (start date) of the last update to the resource, when the resource is being added to.
The date range (end date) of the last update to the resource, when the resource is being added to.
The date during which the dataset or resource is accurate.
The date range (start date) during which the dataset or resource is accurate.
The date range (end date) during which the dataset or resource is accurate.

The date the resource is removed.
 It is good practice to include a description that indicates the reason for the retraction or withdrawal.
Other date that does not fit into an existing category.
